{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Let's talk about billions."},{"time":3000,"text":"Let's talk about"},{"time":6000,"text":"past and future billions."},{"time":9000,"text":"We know"},{"time":11000,"text":"that about 106 billion people"},{"time":14000,"text":"have ever lived."},{"time":16000,"text":"And we know that most of them are dead."},{"time":19000,"text":"And we also know"},{"time":21000,"text":"that most of them live or lived in Asia."},{"time":23000,"text":"And we also know"},{"time":25000,"text":"that most of them were or are very poor --"},{"time":29000,"text":"did not live for very long."},{"time":32000,"text":"Let's talk about billions."},{"time":35000,"text":"Let's talk about"},{"time":37000,"text":"the 195,000 billion dollars of wealth"},{"time":41000,"text":"in the world today."},{"time":44000,"text":"We know that most of that wealth"},{"time":47000,"text":"was made after the year 1800."},{"time":50000,"text":"And we know that most of it"},{"time":53000,"text":"is currently owned"},{"time":55000,"text":"by people we might call Westerners:"},{"time":59000,"text":"Europeans, North Americans, Australasians."},{"time":63000,"text":"19 percent of the world's population today,"},{"time":66000,"text":"Westerners own two-thirds of its wealth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70000,"text":"Economic historians"},{"time":72000,"text":"call this \"The Great Divergence.\""},{"time":75000,"text":"And this slide here"},{"time":77000,"text":"is the best simplification"},{"time":79000,"text":"of the Great Divergence story"},{"time":81000,"text":"I can offer you."},{"time":83000,"text":"It's basically two ratios"},{"time":85000,"text":"of per capita GDP,"},{"time":87000,"text":"per capita gross domestic product,"},{"time":90000,"text":"so average income."},{"time":92000,"text":"One, the red line,"},{"time":94000,"text":"is the ratio of British to Indian"},{"time":96000,"text":"per capita income."},{"time":98000,"text":"And the blue line"},{"time":100000,"text":"is the ratio of American to Chinese."},{"time":103000,"text":"And this chart goes back to 1500."},{"time":105000,"text":"And you can see here"},{"time":107000,"text":"that there's an exponential Great Divergence."},{"time":110000,"text":"They start off pretty close together."},{"time":112000,"text":"In fact, in 1500,"},{"time":114000,"text":"the average Chinese was richer than the average North American."},{"time":118000,"text":"When you get to the 1970s,"},{"time":121000,"text":"which is where this chart ends,"},{"time":123000,"text":"the average Briton is more than 10 times richer"},{"time":125000,"text":"than the average Indian."},{"time":127000,"text":"And that's allowing"},{"time":129000,"text":"for differences in the cost of living."},{"time":131000,"text":"It's based on purchasing power parity."},{"time":134000,"text":"The average American"},{"time":136000,"text":"is nearly 20 times richer"},{"time":138000,"text":"than the average Chinese"},{"time":140000,"text":"by the 1970s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142000,"text":"So why?"},{"time":145000,"text":"This wasn't just an economic story."},{"time":148000,"text":"If you take the 10 countries"},{"time":150000,"text":"that went on to become"},{"time":153000,"text":"the Western empires,"},{"time":155000,"text":"in 1500 they were really quite tiny --"},{"time":158000,"text":"five percent of the world's land surface,"},{"time":160000,"text":"16 percent of its population,"},{"time":162000,"text":"maybe 20 percent of its income."},{"time":165000,"text":"By 1913,"},{"time":167000,"text":"these 10 countries, plus the United States,"},{"time":170000,"text":"controlled vast global empires --"},{"time":173000,"text":"58 percent of the world's territory,"},{"time":175000,"text":"about the same percentage of its population,"},{"time":178000,"text":"and a really huge, nearly three-quarters share"},{"time":181000,"text":"of global economic output."},{"time":183000,"text":"And notice, most of that went to the motherland,"},{"time":187000,"text":"to the imperial metropoles,"},{"time":189000,"text":"not to their colonial possessions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193000,"text":"Now you can't just blame this on imperialism --"},{"time":195000,"text":"though many people have tried to do so --"},{"time":198000,"text":"for two reasons."},{"time":201000,"text":"One, empire was the least original thing"},{"time":204000,"text":"that the West did after 1500."},{"time":207000,"text":"Everybody did empire."},{"time":210000,"text":"They beat preexisting Oriental empires"},{"time":213000,"text":"like the Mughals and the Ottomans."},{"time":215000,"text":"So it really doesn't look like empire is a great explanation"},{"time":218000,"text":"for the Great Divergence."},{"time":220000,"text":"In any case, as you may remember,"},{"time":222000,"text":"the Great Divergence reaches its zenith in the 1970s,"},{"time":225000,"text":"some considerable time after decolonization."},{"time":229000,"text":"This is not a new question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231000,"text":"Samuel Johnson,"},{"time":233000,"text":"the great lexicographer,"},{"time":235000,"text":"[posed] it through his character Rasselas"},{"time":238000,"text":"in his novel \"Rasselas, Prince of Abissinia,\""},{"time":241000,"text":"published in 1759."},{"time":244000,"text":"\"By what means are the Europeans thus powerful;"},{"time":247000,"text":"or why, since they can so easily visit Asia and Africa"},{"time":250000,"text":"for trade or conquest,"},{"time":253000,"text":"cannot the Asiaticks and Africans"},{"time":255000,"text":"invade their coasts,"},{"time":257000,"text":"plant colonies in their ports,"},{"time":259000,"text":"and give laws to their natural princes?"},{"time":262000,"text":"The same wind that carries them back"},{"time":265000,"text":"would bring us thither?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":267000,"text":"That's a great question."},{"time":269000,"text":"And you know what,"},{"time":271000,"text":"it was also being asked at roughly the same time"},{"time":273000,"text":"by the Resterners -- by the people in the rest of the world --"},{"time":276000,"text":"like Ibrahim Muteferrika,"},{"time":279000,"text":"an Ottoman official,"},{"time":281000,"text":"the man who introduced printing, very belatedly,"},{"time":284000,"text":"to the Ottoman Empire --"},{"time":286000,"text":"who said in a book published in 1731,"},{"time":289000,"text":"\"Why do Christian nations which were so weak in the past"},{"time":291000,"text":"compared with Muslim nations"},{"time":293000,"text":"begin to dominate so many lands in modern times"},{"time":297000,"text":"and even defeat the once victorious Ottoman armies?\""},{"time":301000,"text":"Unlike Rasselas,"},{"time":303000,"text":"Muteferrika had an answer to that question,"},{"time":305000,"text":"which was correct."},{"time":308000,"text":"He said it was \"because they have laws and rules"},{"time":312000,"text":"invented by reason.\""},{"time":316000,"text":"It's not geography."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319000,"text":"You may think we can explain the Great Divergence"},{"time":321000,"text":"in terms of geography."},{"time":323000,"text":"We know that's wrong,"},{"time":325000,"text":"because we conducted two great natural experiments in the 20th century"},{"time":327000,"text":"to see if geography mattered more than institutions."},{"time":329000,"text":"We took all the Germans,"},{"time":332000,"text":"we divided them roughly in two,"},{"time":334000,"text":"and we gave the ones in the East communism,"},{"time":337000,"text":"and you see the result."},{"time":340000,"text":"Within an incredibly short period of time,"},{"time":342000,"text":"people living in the German Democratic Republic"},{"time":344000,"text":"produced Trabants, the Trabbi,"},{"time":347000,"text":"one of the world's worst ever cars,"},{"time":350000,"text":"while people in the West produced the Mercedes Benz."},{"time":353000,"text":"If you still don't believe me,"},{"time":355000,"text":"we conducted the experiment also in the Korean Peninsula."},{"time":357000,"text":"And we decided we'd take Koreans"},{"time":359000,"text":"in roughly the same geographical place"},{"time":361000,"text":"with, notice, the same basic traditional culture,"},{"time":365000,"text":"and we divided them in two, and we gave the Northerners communism."},{"time":368000,"text":"And the result is an even bigger divergence"},{"time":371000,"text":"in a very short space of time"},{"time":373000,"text":"than happened in Germany."},{"time":375000,"text":"Not a big divergence in terms of uniform design for border guards admittedly,"},{"time":379000,"text":"but in almost every other respect,"},{"time":381000,"text":"it's a huge divergence."},{"time":383000,"text":"Which leads me to think"},{"time":385000,"text":"that neither geography nor national character,"},{"time":387000,"text":"popular explanations for this kind of thing,"},{"time":389000,"text":"are really significant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392000,"text":"It's the ideas."},{"time":394000,"text":"It's the institutions."},{"time":396000,"text":"This must be true"},{"time":398000,"text":"because a Scotsman said it."},{"time":400000,"text":"And I think I'm the only Scotsman here at the Edinburgh TED."},{"time":403000,"text":"So let me just explain to you"},{"time":405000,"text":"that the smartest man ever was a Scotsman."},{"time":408000,"text":"He was Adam Smith --"},{"time":410000,"text":"not Billy Connolly, not Sean Connery --"},{"time":413000,"text":"though he is very smart indeed."},{"time":416000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":419000,"text":"Smith -- and I want you to go"},{"time":421000,"text":"and bow down before his statue in the Royal Mile;"},{"time":424000,"text":"it's a wonderful statue --"},{"time":426000,"text":"Smith, in the \"Wealth of Nations\""},{"time":428000,"text":"published in 1776 --"},{"time":430000,"text":"that's the most important thing that happened that year ..."},{"time":433000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":436000,"text":"You bet."},{"time":439000,"text":"There was a little local difficulty in some of our minor colonies, but ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":444000,"text":"\"China seems to have been long stationary,"},{"time":446000,"text":"and probably long ago acquired that full complement of riches"},{"time":449000,"text":"which is consistent with the nature of its laws and institutions."},{"time":453000,"text":"But this complement may be much inferior"},{"time":455000,"text":"to what, with other laws and institutions,"},{"time":458000,"text":"the nature of its soil, climate, and situation"},{"time":460000,"text":"might admit of.\""},{"time":462000,"text":"That is so right and so cool."},{"time":464000,"text":"And he said it such a long time ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467000,"text":"But you know, this is a TED audience,"},{"time":470000,"text":"and if I keep talking about institutions,"},{"time":472000,"text":"you're going to turn off."},{"time":474000,"text":"So I'm going to translate this into language that you can understand."},{"time":478000,"text":"Let's call them the killer apps."},{"time":482000,"text":"I want to explain to you that there were six killer apps"},{"time":485000,"text":"that set the West apart from the rest."},{"time":488000,"text":"And they're kind of like the apps on your phone,"},{"time":490000,"text":"in the sense that they look quite simple."},{"time":492000,"text":"They're just icons; you click on them."},{"time":494000,"text":"But behind the icon, there's complex code."},{"time":497000,"text":"It's the same with institutions."},{"time":499000,"text":"There are six"},{"time":501000,"text":"which I think explain the Great Divergence."},{"time":504000,"text":"One, competition."},{"time":506000,"text":"Two, the scientific revolution."},{"time":508000,"text":"Three, property rights."},{"time":510000,"text":"Four, modern medicine."},{"time":512000,"text":"Five, the consumer society."},{"time":514000,"text":"And six, the work ethic."},{"time":516000,"text":"You can play a game and try and think of one I've missed at,"},{"time":518000,"text":"or try and boil it down to just four,"},{"time":521000,"text":"but you'll lose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":525000,"text":"Let me very briefly tell you what I mean by this,"},{"time":528000,"text":"synthesizing the work of many economic historians"},{"time":531000,"text":"in the process."},{"time":533000,"text":"Competition means,"},{"time":535000,"text":"not only were there a hundred different political units in Europe in 1500,"},{"time":537000,"text":"but within each of these units,"},{"time":539000,"text":"there was competition between corporations as well as sovereigns."},{"time":543000,"text":"The ancestor of the modern corporation, the City of London Corporation,"},{"time":546000,"text":"existed in the 12th century."},{"time":548000,"text":"Nothing like this existed in China,"},{"time":550000,"text":"where there was one monolithic state"},{"time":552000,"text":"covering a fifth of humanity,"},{"time":554000,"text":"and anyone with any ambition"},{"time":556000,"text":"had to pass one standardized examination,"},{"time":558000,"text":"which took three days and was very difficult"},{"time":560000,"text":"and involved memorizing vast numbers of characters"},{"time":563000,"text":"and very complex Confucian essay writing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567000,"text":"The scientific revolution was different"},{"time":570000,"text":"from the science that had been achieved in the Oriental world"},{"time":573000,"text":"in a number of crucial ways,"},{"time":575000,"text":"the most important being"},{"time":577000,"text":"that, through the experimental method,"},{"time":579000,"text":"it gave men control over nature in a way that had not been possible before."},{"time":582000,"text":"Example: Benjamin Robins's extraordinary application"},{"time":586000,"text":"of Newtonian physics to ballistics."},{"time":589000,"text":"Once you do that,"},{"time":591000,"text":"your artillery becomes accurate."},{"time":594000,"text":"Think of what that means."},{"time":596000,"text":"That really was a killer application."},{"time":598000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":601000,"text":"Meanwhile, there's no scientific revolution anywhere else."},{"time":604000,"text":"The Ottoman Empire's not that far from Europe,"},{"time":606000,"text":"but there's no scientific revolution there."},{"time":608000,"text":"In fact, they demolish Taqi al-Din's observatory,"},{"time":611000,"text":"because it's considered blasphemous"},{"time":613000,"text":"to inquire into the mind of God."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616000,"text":"Property rights: It's not the democracy, folks;"},{"time":619000,"text":"it's having the rule of law based on private property rights."},{"time":622000,"text":"That's what makes the difference"},{"time":624000,"text":"between North America and South America."},{"time":626000,"text":"You could turn up in North America"},{"time":628000,"text":"having signed a deed of indenture"},{"time":630000,"text":"saying, \"I'll work for nothing for five years."},{"time":632000,"text":"You just have to feed me.\""},{"time":634000,"text":"But at the end of it, you've got a hundred acres of land."},{"time":637000,"text":"That's the land grant"},{"time":639000,"text":"on the bottom half of the slide."},{"time":641000,"text":"That's not possible in Latin America"},{"time":644000,"text":"where land is held onto"},{"time":646000,"text":"by a tiny elite descended from the conquistadors."},{"time":648000,"text":"And you can see here the huge divergence"},{"time":650000,"text":"that happens in property ownership between North and South."},{"time":653000,"text":"Most people in rural North America"},{"time":655000,"text":"owned some land by 1900."},{"time":658000,"text":"Hardly anyone in South America did."},{"time":660000,"text":"That's another killer app."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663000,"text":"Modern medicine in the late 19th century"},{"time":665000,"text":"began to make major breakthroughs"},{"time":667000,"text":"against the infectious diseases that killed a lot of people."},{"time":669000,"text":"And this was another killer app --"},{"time":671000,"text":"the very opposite of a killer,"},{"time":673000,"text":"because it doubled, and then more than doubled, human life expectancy."},{"time":676000,"text":"It even did that"},{"time":678000,"text":"in the European empires."},{"time":680000,"text":"Even in places like Senegal,"},{"time":682000,"text":"beginning in the early 20th century,"},{"time":684000,"text":"there were major breakthroughs in public health,"},{"time":686000,"text":"and life expectancy began to rise."},{"time":688000,"text":"It doesn't rise any faster"},{"time":690000,"text":"after these countries become independent."},{"time":692000,"text":"The empires weren't all bad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":694000,"text":"The consumer society is what you need"},{"time":696000,"text":"for the Industrial Revolution to have a point."},{"time":699000,"text":"You need people to want to wear tons of clothes."},{"time":701000,"text":"You've all bought an article of clothing in the last month;"},{"time":703000,"text":"I guarantee it."},{"time":705000,"text":"That's the consumer society,"},{"time":707000,"text":"and it propels economic growth"},{"time":709000,"text":"more than even technological change itself."},{"time":712000,"text":"Japan was the first non-Western society"},{"time":714000,"text":"to embrace it."},{"time":716000,"text":"The alternative,"},{"time":718000,"text":"which was proposed by Mahatma Gandhi,"},{"time":720000,"text":"was to institutionalize and make poverty permanent."},{"time":723000,"text":"Very few Indians today"},{"time":725000,"text":"wish that India had gone down"},{"time":727000,"text":"Mahatma Gandhi's road."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730000,"text":"Finally, the work ethic."},{"time":732000,"text":"Max Weber thought that was peculiarly Protestant."},{"time":735000,"text":"He was wrong."},{"time":737000,"text":"Any culture can get the work ethic"},{"time":739000,"text":"if the institutions are there"},{"time":741000,"text":"to create the incentive to work."},{"time":743000,"text":"We know this"},{"time":745000,"text":"because today the work ethic"},{"time":747000,"text":"is no longer a Protestant, Western phenomenon."},{"time":750000,"text":"In fact, the West has lost its work ethic."},{"time":753000,"text":"Today, the average Korean"},{"time":756000,"text":"works a thousand hours more a year"},{"time":760000,"text":"than the average German --"},{"time":762000,"text":"a thousand."},{"time":764000,"text":"And this is part"},{"time":766000,"text":"of a really extraordinary phenomenon,"},{"time":769000,"text":"and that is the end of the Great Divergence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772000,"text":"Who's got the work ethic now?"},{"time":774000,"text":"Take a look at mathematical attainment"},{"time":777000,"text":"by 15 year-olds."},{"time":779000,"text":"At the top of the international league table"},{"time":781000,"text":"according to the latest PISA study,"},{"time":784000,"text":"is the Shanghai district of China."},{"time":786000,"text":"The gap between Shanghai"},{"time":788000,"text":"and the United Kingdom and the United States"},{"time":791000,"text":"is as big as the gap between the U.K. and the U.S."},{"time":794000,"text":"and Albania and Tunisia."},{"time":797000,"text":"You probably assume"},{"time":799000,"text":"that because the iPhone was designed in California"},{"time":801000,"text":"but assembled in China"},{"time":803000,"text":"that the West still leads in terms of technological innovation."},{"time":806000,"text":"You're wrong."},{"time":808000,"text":"In terms of patents,"},{"time":810000,"text":"there's no question that the East is ahead."},{"time":812000,"text":"Not only has Japan been ahead for some time,"},{"time":815000,"text":"South Korea has gone into third place,"},{"time":818000,"text":"and China is just about to overtake Germany."},{"time":821000,"text":"Why?"},{"time":823000,"text":"Because the killer apps can be downloaded."},{"time":825000,"text":"It's open source."},{"time":827000,"text":"Any society can adopt these institutions,"},{"time":829000,"text":"and when they do,"},{"time":831000,"text":"they achieve what the West achieved after 1500 --"},{"time":835000,"text":"only faster."}]},{"cues":[{"time":837000,"text":"This is the Great Reconvergence,"},{"time":839000,"text":"and it's the biggest story of your lifetime."},{"time":843000,"text":"Because it's on your watch that this is happening."},{"time":846000,"text":"It's our generation"},{"time":848000,"text":"that is witnessing the end of Western predominance."},{"time":850000,"text":"The average American used to be more than 20 times richer"},{"time":852000,"text":"than the average Chinese."},{"time":854000,"text":"Now it's just five times,"},{"time":856000,"text":"and soon it will be 2.5 times."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858000,"text":"So I want to end with three questions"},{"time":861000,"text":"for the future billions,"},{"time":863000,"text":"just ahead of 2016,"},{"time":866000,"text":"when the United States will lose its place"},{"time":868000,"text":"as number one economy to China."},{"time":871000,"text":"The first is, can you delete these apps,"},{"time":875000,"text":"and are we in the process of doing so"},{"time":877000,"text":"in the Western world?"},{"time":879000,"text":"The second question is,"},{"time":881000,"text":"does the sequencing of the download matter?"},{"time":885000,"text":"And could Africa get that sequencing wrong?"},{"time":890000,"text":"One obvious implication of modern economic history"},{"time":892000,"text":"is that it's quite hard to transition to democracy"},{"time":895000,"text":"before you've established"},{"time":897000,"text":"secure private property rights."},{"time":900000,"text":"Warning: that may not work."},{"time":903000,"text":"And third, can China do without"},{"time":905000,"text":"killer app number three?"},{"time":907000,"text":"That's the one that John Locke systematized"},{"time":911000,"text":"when he said that freedom was rooted in private property rights"},{"time":915000,"text":"and the protection of law."},{"time":917000,"text":"That's the basis"},{"time":919000,"text":"for the Western model"},{"time":921000,"text":"of representative government."},{"time":924000,"text":"Now this picture shows the demolition"},{"time":926000,"text":"of the Chinese artist Ai Weiwei's studio"},{"time":929000,"text":"in Shanghai earlier this year."},{"time":931000,"text":"He's now free again,"},{"time":933000,"text":"having been detained, as you know, for some time."},{"time":935000,"text":"But I don't think his studio has been rebuilt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940000,"text":"Winston Churchill once defined civilization"},{"time":944000,"text":"in a lecture he gave in the fateful year of 1938."},{"time":948000,"text":"And I think these words really nail it:"},{"time":951000,"text":"\"It means a society based upon the opinion of civilians."},{"time":955000,"text":"It means that violence, the rule of warriors and despotic chiefs,"},{"time":958000,"text":"the conditions of camps and warfare, of riot and tyranny,"},{"time":961000,"text":"give place to parliaments where laws are made,"},{"time":964000,"text":"and independent courts of justice"},{"time":966000,"text":"in which over long periods those laws are maintained."},{"time":969000,"text":"That is civilization --"},{"time":971000,"text":"and in its soil grow continually"},{"time":973000,"text":"freedom, comfort and culture,\""},{"time":976000,"text":"what all TEDsters care about most."},{"time":980000,"text":"\"When civilization reigns in any country,"},{"time":983000,"text":"a wider and less harassed life"},{"time":986000,"text":"is afforded to the masses of the people.\""},{"time":989000,"text":"That's so true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":993000,"text":"I don't think the decline of Western civilization"},{"time":996000,"text":"is inevitable,"},{"time":998000,"text":"because I don't think history operates"},{"time":1001000,"text":"in this kind of life-cycle model,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"beautifully illustrated by Thomas Cole's"},{"time":1005000,"text":"\"Course of Empire\" paintings."},{"time":1008000,"text":"That's not the way history works."},{"time":1011000,"text":"That's not the way the West rose,"},{"time":1013000,"text":"and I don't think it's the way the West will fall."},{"time":1016000,"text":"The West may collapse very suddenly."},{"time":1019000,"text":"Complex civilizations do that,"},{"time":1022000,"text":"because they operate, most of the time,"},{"time":1024000,"text":"on the edge of chaos."},{"time":1026000,"text":"That's one of the most profound insights"},{"time":1029000,"text":"to come out of the historical study of complex institutions"},{"time":1032000,"text":"like civilizations."},{"time":1035000,"text":"No, we may hang on,"},{"time":1037000,"text":"despite the huge burdens of debt that we've accumulated,"},{"time":1041000,"text":"despite the evidence that we've lost our work ethic"},{"time":1044000,"text":"and other parts of our historical mojo."},{"time":1047000,"text":"But one thing is for sure,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"the Great Divergence"},{"time":1051000,"text":"is over, folks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1053000,"text":"Thanks very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1055000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1080000,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Niall,"},{"time":1082000,"text":"I am just curious"},{"time":1084000,"text":"about your take on the other region of the world that's booming,"},{"time":1087000,"text":"which is Latin America."},{"time":1090000,"text":"What's your view on that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1093000,"text":"Niall Ferguson: Well I really am not just talking"},{"time":1095000,"text":"about the rise of the East;"},{"time":1097000,"text":"I'm talking about the rise of the Rest,"},{"time":1099000,"text":"and that includes South America."},{"time":1101000,"text":"I once asked one of my colleagues at Harvard,"},{"time":1103000,"text":"\"Hey, is South America part of the West?\""},{"time":1105000,"text":"He was an expert in Latin American history."},{"time":1107000,"text":"He said, \"I don't know; I'll have to think about that.\""},{"time":1109000,"text":"That tells you something really important."},{"time":1111000,"text":"I think if you look at what is happening in Brazil in particular,"},{"time":1113000,"text":"but also Chile,"},{"time":1115000,"text":"which was in many ways the one that led the way"},{"time":1118000,"text":"in transforming the institutions of economic life,"},{"time":1121000,"text":"there's a very bright future indeed."},{"time":1124000,"text":"So my story really is"},{"time":1126000,"text":"as much about that convergence in the Americas"},{"time":1129000,"text":"as it's a convergence story in Eurasia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1131000,"text":"BG: And there is this impression"},{"time":1133000,"text":"that North America and Europe"},{"time":1135000,"text":"are not really paying attention"},{"time":1137000,"text":"to these trends."},{"time":1139000,"text":"Mostly they're worried about each other."},{"time":1142000,"text":"The Americans think that the European model is going to crumble tomorrow."},{"time":1145000,"text":"The Europeans think that the American budget is going to explode tomorrow."},{"time":1148000,"text":"And that's all we seem to be caring about recently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1151000,"text":"NF: I think the fiscal crisis"},{"time":1153000,"text":"that we see in the developed World right now -- both sides of the Atlantic --"},{"time":1156000,"text":"is essentially the same thing"},{"time":1158000,"text":"taking different forms"},{"time":1160000,"text":"in terms of political culture."},{"time":1162000,"text":"And it's a crisis that has its structural facet --"},{"time":1166000,"text":"it's partly to do with demographics."},{"time":1168000,"text":"But it's also, of course, to do with the massive crisis"},{"time":1171000,"text":"that followed excessive leverage,"},{"time":1173000,"text":"excessive borrowing in the private sector."},{"time":1175000,"text":"That crisis,"},{"time":1177000,"text":"which has been the focus of so much attention, including by me,"},{"time":1180000,"text":"I think is an epiphenomenon."},{"time":1182000,"text":"The financial crisis is really a relatively small historic phenomenon,"},{"time":1185000,"text":"which has just accelerated"},{"time":1187000,"text":"this huge shift,"},{"time":1189000,"text":"which ends half a millennium of Western ascendancy."},{"time":1191000,"text":"I think that's its real importance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1193000,"text":"BG: Niall, thank you. (NF: Thank you very much, Bruno.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1195000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}